This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new imitation learning method that utilizes automatic rankings to improve performance. The paper also discusses the theoretical basis for why ranked demonstrations can lead to better-than-demonstrator performance. 

The paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics) as imitation learning is a common technique used in these fields. 

Additionally, the paper includes experiments on standard Atari and MuJoCo benchmarks, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
